        "Source": "ANSA"
      }
    ],
    "Description": "An update for kernel package is now avaiable for Anolis OS 8 that fix CVE-2022-3176:\n\nCVE-2022-3176:\nThere exists a use-after-free in io_uring in the Linux kernel. Signalfd_poll() and binder_poll() use a waitqueue whose lifetime is the current task. It will send a POLLFREE notification to all waiters before the queue is freed. Unfortunately, the io_uring poll doesn't handle POLLFREE. This allows a use-after-free to occur if a signalfd or binder fd is polled with io_uring poll, and the waitqueue gets freed. We recommend upgrading past commit fc78b2fc21f10c4c9c4d5d659a685710ffa63659",
    "Advisory": {
